<paragraph blockId="17.[336,1289,637,731]" pageId="17" pageNumber="114">
Taxonomic position – The new species, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Papp" authorityYear="2013" box="[878,1186,637,663]" class="Insecta" family="Braconidae" genus="Mirax" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="114" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="politus" subGenus="Centistidea">
<emphasis box="[878,1186,637,663]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="114">Mirax (Centistidea) politus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, is nearest to 
<taxonomicName authority="Papp, 2013" authorityName="Papp" authorityYear="2013" box="[407,593,671,697]" class="Insecta" family="Braconidae" genus="Mirax" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="114" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ubangus" status="sp. n." subGenus="Centistidea">
<emphasis box="[407,593,671,697]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="114">M. (C.) ubangus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[599,664,672,698]" pageId="17" pageNumber="114" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
considering their polished body and dark corporal colour, the two species are distinguished as follows:
</paragraph>
